review_blob: Pours dark with a light tan head. Sweeter than most pecan porters but I really like how this beer finishes.
This beer keep getting better and better. The smell of the toasted coconut is upfront but drinking it you dont get it till on the back end. Really enjoy drinking this beer on a nice sunny day.
Pours Dark with a nice khaki head. Chocolate flavor and finishes with a nice bitterness from the coco nibs. The alcohol is well hidden. I can drink this beer year round
